# Zarubino, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Zarubino () is a rural locality (a selo) in Dzhidinsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 273 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Zarubino is located 71&nbsp;km east of Petropavlovka (the district's administrative centre) by road. Dyrestuy and Dzhida are the nearest rural localities.
